Vemard Africa FC, a Nationwide League One (NLO) side will play host to Enyimba FC of Aba on Feb. 14 in their first major football match at their new base, NEROS Stadium in Orumba North Council Area of Anambra state. Vemard, previously based in Enugu is packaging the grade A encounter with Peoples Elephant as the highpoint of the sensitisation activities to announce their arrival to the NEROS, Nanka as their new home. Akonam Obiefuna, Director of Scorecard Productions, Consultants to Vemard Africa FC said former Super Eagles stars, Taribo West, Victor Ikpeba, others would participate in the game as special appearances. Obiefuna said the club had to win the NLO and plying its trade in the Nigeria National League in 2020/2021 season as its immediate objectives. Fulfill Oyo 2019 coalition agreements, ADC candidates charge… PDP governors congratulate Duoye Diri Proscribed NURTW leaders warn Oyo govt against introduction… Reps demand records on CBN revenues, capital projects ALSO READ: Entrepreneur, Oladipupo tasks Nigerian youths on honesty A popular Rap Artist, Slow Dog will also thrill football fans with live music performance. He said recruitment of talented football stars would follow soon after the sensitisation match to beef up the squad ahead of the season as well as giving them the opportunity for international exposure. TribuneOnline gathered that VEMARD Africa Football Club is an NLO league side with these initial ambitions which include to win the NLO and compete in NNL come 2020/2021 season,” he said. The consultant said other activities of the day would include the unveiling of club media officer, social media handles and awareness for the players scouting programme. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FR